###############    test local hint   #################
## partition-wise join ==> pull to local
explain outline select /*+ leading(t1 t2) */ * from t1, t2 where c1 = d1;
Query Plan
=============================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                 |NAME    |EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
-------------------------------------------------------------
|0 |PX COORDINATOR           |        |10      |38          |
|1 |└─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR     |:EX10000|10      |32          |
|2 |  └─PX PARTITION ITERATOR|        |10      |19          |
|3 |    └─HASH JOIN          |        |10      |19          |
|4 |      ├─TABLE FULL SCAN  |t1      |10      |7           |
|5 |      └─TABLE FULL SCAN  |t2      |20      |8           |
=============================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([INTERNAL_FUNCTION(t1.c1, t1.c2, t2.d1, t2.d2)]), filter(nil), rowset=256
  1 - output([INTERNAL_FUNCTION(t1.c1, t1.c2, t2.d1, t2.d2)]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      dop=1
  2 - output([t1.c1], [t2.d1], [t1.c2], [t2.d2]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      partition wise, force partition granule
  3 - output([t1.c1], [t2.d1], [t1.c2], [t2.d2]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      equal_conds([t1.c1 = t2.d1]), other_conds(nil)
  4 - output([t1.c1], [t1.c2]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      access([t1.c1], [t1.c2]), partitions(p[0-2])
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([t1.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
  5 - output([t2.d1], [t2.d2]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      access([t2.d1], [t2.d2]), partitions(p[0-2])
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([t2.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
